  "id": "phekb-copd-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "copd",
  "name": "COPD - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying COPD patients via Condition + MedicationRequest. Path C (med only without dx) reflects bronchodilator use without formal COPD diagnosis (often asthma cross-indication).",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete COPD patient population for a chronic disease management program. Some patients have a coded COPD or emphysema diagnosis. Others are on inhaled bronchodilators (albuterol, salmeterol) for chronic respiratory symptoms but may not have a formal COPD diagnosis. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis and bronchodilator medications — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all COPD patients.",
    "broad": "Find all COPD patients — by diagnosis (COPD or emphysema) or by inhaled bronchodilator prescriptions (albuterol, salmeterol). Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run two queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|13645005,http://snomed.info/sct|87433001 — COPD/emphysema dx. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|435,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|36117 — bronchodilators. Union the patient IDs."
  },
